<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0d9fd2e4-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007"><num value="21007">§ 21007.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0d9fd2e5-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to amounts transferred under <ref href="/us/usc/t52/s20904/c">section 20904(c) of this title</ref>, there are authorized to be appropriated for requirements payments under this subpart the following amounts:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0d9fd2e6-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> For fiscal year 2003, $1,400,000,000.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0d9fd2e7-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> For fiscal year 2004, $1,000,000,000.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0d9fd2e8-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> For fiscal year 2005, $600,000,000.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0d9fd2e9-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/a/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> For fiscal year 2010 and subsequent fiscal years, such sums as are necessary for purposes of making requirements payments to States to carry out the activities described in <ref href="/us/usc/t52/s21001/b/3">section 21001(b)(3) of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0d9fd2ea-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21007/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Availability</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any amounts appropriated pursuant to the authority of subsection (a) shall remain available without fiscal year limitation until expended.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0d9fd2eb-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tII/s257">Pub. L. 107–252, title II, § 257</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1697">116 Stat. 1697</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/84/dA/tV/s588/c">Pub. L. 111–84, div. A, title V, § 588(c)</ref>, <date date="2009-10-28">Oct. 28, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/2334">123 Stat. 2334</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0d9fd2ec-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0d9fd2ed-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id0d9fd2ee-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s15407">section 15407 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id0d9fd2ef-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2009—Subsec. (a)(4). <ref href="/us/pl/111/84">Pub. L. 111–84</ref> added par. (4).</p>
</note>
</notes>
